snippet: Despite doubts about his candidacy, Joe Biden begins the race with substantial support from three key constituencies in his native state, a place the Democrats can’t afford to lose again.
lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — The case for Joseph R. Biden Jr. has always come down to Pennsylvania.
abstract: Despite doubts about his candidacy, Joe Biden begins the race with substantial support from three key constituencies in his native state, a place the Democrats can’t afford to lose again.

headline_main: In Pennsylvania, Joe Biden Finds Support Where He Most Needs It
headline_print_headline: Biden’s Appeal Taps the Voters His Party Needs

snippet: Four years ago, Barack Obama gently discouraged him from running for president, but Joseph R. Biden Jr. is back and presenting himself as Mr. Obama’s natural heir.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Barack Obama did not think Joseph R. Biden Jr. should run for president — he hardly needed to say it out loud for aides to understand that. The trick that summer of 2015 was finding a way to nudge Mr. Biden to stay out of the race without looking as if he was nudging Mr. Biden to stay out of the race.

snippet: Mr. Sanders’s campaign kicked off its national organizing program Saturday with what it says are roughly 5,000 events across every state.
lead_paragraph: Just days after former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. became the 20th candidate to join the Democratic presidential race, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont readied what he hoped would be his latest show of force: thousands of house parties across the country.

snippet: Anita Hill reflected on the 1991 Clarence Thomas hearings and the role former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. played in them.
lead_paragraph: Anita Hill spoke by phone this week with The New York Times, reflecting on the Clarence Thomas hearings in 1991 that put a spotlight on sexual harassment and treatment of accusers.
abstract: Anita Hill reflected on the 1991 Clarence Thomas hearings and the role former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. played in them.

headline_main: Excerpts From Anita Hill’s Interview With The Times

snippet: Susan Bro, whose daughter was killed at a white supremacist rally in Charlottesville, Va., said she warned Mr. Biden to tread carefully around the episode and spoke with him about grief.
lead_paragraph: Around 7:20 a.m. on Thursday, Susan Bro began getting text messages. Was she all right? How did she feel about what Joe Biden had done?

snippet: Mr. Biden raised more in his first 24 hours than any other candidate, easing concerns among some supporters over his ability to raise money.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign announced Friday that it had raised $6.3 million in its opening 24 hours, surpassing the first-day totals of his rivals and easing concerns among some supporters over whether he would be able to compete financially in the Democratic primary.
